@class Name: Eclipse.cs
@brief Calculating eclipse event.

This class provides the fuction for calculating eclipse events.

@author: Unseob Lee (uslee@satreci.com)
@create date 2012.11.09
@version 1.0
@Revision History

1. Eclipse Result Review
2019-09-06 : JongSoo Park(jspark@satreci.com)
- Compared with the result of STK, eclipse time was calculated longer.
- This class uses only the equator radius of the earth as blocker, but STK probably calculates eclipse time by applying the earth ellipsoid model (not constant radius).
- It was confirmed that eclipse time difference occurred due to this cause.
- In conclusion, to conservatively calculate the eclipse time, we decided to keep using the Earth's equator radius for this class.
- Users of this class should keep in mind that eclipse time can be calculated longer than it actually is.
- More detail information can be checked from following confluence page : http://sigma:9091/display/GSDModule/08.Event+Prediction


